# MCP Tools: vercel

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

### add_toolbar_reaction
Add an emoji reaction to a message in a toolbar thread.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| threadId | string | Yes | - | Thread ID containing the message |
| messageId | string | Yes | - | Message ID to react to |
| teamId | string | Yes | - | Team ID or slug |
| emoji | string | Yes | - | Emoji reaction |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "vercel", toolName: "add_toolbar_reaction", arguments: { threadId: "thread_123", messageId: "msg_456", teamId: "team_abc", emoji: "👍" } })

### edit_toolbar_message
Edit an existing message in a toolbar thread.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| threadId | string | Yes | - | Thread ID containing the message |
| messageId | string | Yes | - | Message ID to edit |
| teamId | string | Yes | - | Team ID or slug |
| markdown | string | Yes | - | Updated message content |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "vercel", toolName: "edit_toolbar_message", arguments: { threadId: "thread_123", messageId: "msg_456", teamId: "team_abc", markdown: "Updated comment" } })

### reply_to_toolbar_thread
