### get_runtime_errors
Get grouped runtime error clusters for a project.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| projectId | string | Yes | - | Project ID |
| teamId | string | Yes | - | Team ID or slug |
| since | string | No | - | Start time (ISO or relative) |
| until | string | No | - | End time (ISO or relative) |
| routes | string | No | - | Comma-separated route paths |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "vercel", toolName: "get_runtime_errors", arguments: { projectId: "prj_123", teamId: "team_abc", since: "24h" } })

### get_runtime_logs
Get runtime logs for a project or deployment.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| projectId | string | Yes | - | Project ID |
| teamId | string | Yes | - | Team ID or slug |
| deploymentId | string | No | - | Filter by deployment ID or URL |
| environment | string | No | - | production or preview |
| level | array | No | - | error, warning, info, fatal |
| statusCode | string | No | - | HTTP status code filter |
| source | array | No | - | serverless, edge-function, edge-middleware, static |
| since | string | No | - | Start time (ISO or relative) |
| until | string | No | - | End time (ISO or relative) |
| limit | number | No | - | Maximum entries (max 100) |
| query | string | No | - | Full-text search query |
| requestId | string | No | - | Filter by request ID |
| group_by | string | No | - | statusCode, requestPath, route, level, source, deploymentId, branch |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "vercel", toolName: "get_runtime_logs", arguments: { projectId: "prj_123", teamId: "team_abc", environment: "production", limit: 50 } })

